25.body: A disturbance/error is an unknown and uncontrolled input acting on a system. A fault is an unpermitted deviation of at least one characteristic property or parameter of the system from the acceptable/usual/standard operating conditions. A failure is a permanent interruption of a system’s ability to perform a required function under specified operating conditions. Traditional control systems are designed to return the system to normal operations in the presence of disturbances but not in the presence of faults or failures. Fault-tolerant control (FTC) systems refer to control systems that have been designed to explicitly account for some class of specified faults in the closed-loop system. FTC systems must act in the time between a fault and a system failure.
